Oliver Kirkham
Im a software developer, game designer and modder. I
enjoy the whole process of game development, but I
especially enjoy prototyping and rapidly developing
playable content.
My Github account can be found here
My most recent completed project:
Northstar, was developed almost
entirely by me over a period of about a
year.
This project has allowed me to explore
and demonstrate a large part of my
skillset, so it will be the focus of this
portfolio.
It allows users to create their own
multiplayer servers for the game
Titanfall 2, allowing the creation of
custom content and gameplay changes.
Much of Titanfall 2's engine code is in compiled x64 binaries with no
symbols or source code. As such much of the engine code had to be
reverse engineered and hooked into.
To do this, I became proficient in C++17, x64 assembly and reverse
engineering, an undocumented fork of the Squirrel programming language
and many other skills.
Since the project released, it has
received enthusiastic coverage by
several YouTube channels and Gaming
News Outlets, such as PC Gamer and
IGN.
The official Discord server for Northstar
currently has around 45k members,
which were gained over a period of
about 2 months since its release
